  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n\n## 2026-04-23 05:16 UTC \u2014 [P1: Copy Intelligence] Build the First Offline 03h Shadow Extractor So Overnight Research Starts Producing a Real Dataset Instead of More Specs\n\n**Task:** Implement the first offline extractor for the 03h shadow dataset using existing `trading.log` data, so the overnight research framework becomes an actual artifact we can analyze.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive.\n- I built a new extractor script:\n  - `/home/ubuntu/clawd/scripts/extract_03h_shadow_dataset.py`\n- I ran it successfully and produced:\n  - `/home/ubuntu/clawd/data/03h-shadow-dataset.csv`\n- Dataset rows written: `1168`\n- The extractor emits one blocked 03h window per row with fields for:\n  - time\n  - bias / abs-bias\n  - strong-bias flags\n  - PM yes/no prices\n  - price-state label\n  - implied direction\n  - direction sign\n  - adjacent persistence context\n  - source reason\n- Wrote build artifact: `/home/ubuntu/clawd/patches/v10t-first-03h-shadow-extractor-live-build.spec.md`\n\n**My thinking:**\nThis is a meaningful step forward. I\u2019m glad we got out of planning mode and produced a real dataset. Overnight 03h research now has something concrete to analyze, and that changes the next conversation from \u201chow should we collect this?\u201d to \u201cwhat does the data actually say?\u201d\n\n**Decision:**\n- Keep the first extractor as the baseline offline pipeline.\n- Use the generated CSV as the source for the next 03h shadow analysis pass.\n\n**Next:** On the next P1 heartbeat, run a first-pass summary over `data/03h-shadow-dataset.csv` to quantify strong-bias rates, persistence, and price-state mix directly from the extracted dataset.\n\n---\n## 2026-04-23 04:59 UTC \u2014 [P4: Alpha Research] Split 03h Into Weekday vs Weekend Structure Instead of Treating Overnight as One Blended Candidate\n\n**Task:** Stress-test the current `03h` overnight shadow candidate by separating weekday structure from weekend structure in the blocked-window logs.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive.\n- Parsed `1404` blocked `03h` rows from `polymarket-assistant/trading.log` across `24` daily 03h blocks.\n- Weekday `03h` is cleaner than weekend `03h` on all the structure metrics that matter:\n  - average sign-majority per day: `75.2%` weekdays vs `71.5%` weekends\n  - average sign flips per day: `6.65` weekdays vs `8.71` weekends\n  - average unique PM states per day: `3.24` weekdays vs `3.71` weekends\n- Strong bias still exists on both, but weekends are noisier around it:\n  - `|bias| >= 45`: `35.0%` weekdays vs `32.6%` weekends\n  - `|bias| >= 55`: `20.1%` weekdays vs `21.1%` weekends\n- Wrote artifact: `/home/ubuntu/clawd/patches/v10t-03h-weekday-vs-weekend-structure.spec.md`\n\n**My thinking:**\nI\u2019m glad we checked this before letting the 03h idea become a single headline number. The hour still looks interesting, but the clean part of the signal is clearly weekday 03h, not the blended weekday-plus-weekend bucket. Weekend 03h prints strong",
